    "purpose": "Static map of common company names to their employee email domain. Lets find_company_live skip Hunter's company-name->domain resolution when we already know the answer (saves 1 of ~25 monthly Hunter credits per known company) and short-circuits to a direct domain-search.",
    "verification": "Domains researched from official career pages, public engineer profiles (LinkedIn/Twitter), and corporate press releases. Several big-name companies use a distinct internal email domain that does NOT match their marketing site (e.g. Datadog -> datadoghq.com, Notion -> makenotion.com, Block -> block.xyz, JPMorgan -> jpmchase.com). Spot-check before relying for a transactional send. Acquisitions can shift the canonical domain — Twitter -> x.com after the X rebrand, Square -> block.xyz after the Block rebrand.",
    "updated": "2026-05-02",
    "schema": {
      "name": "Canonical company name as a student would type it.",
      "domain": "Email domain (the part after @) used by full-time employees.",
      "aliases": "Other common spellings, short forms, or product names that should resolve to the same domain. Lowercase. Optional.",
      "category": "Loose grouping for filtering/UI. Optional."
    }
